<h2>Processors</h2>
<p>Processors are the core of every UltiBlox project, providing the computing power that drives your ideas. They execute code, make decisions, and control other modules.</p>
<img src="/assets/img/processors.webp" alt="Processors">

<h3>Modular by Nature</h3>
<p>UltiBlox processors are built to fit seamlessly within the ecosystem. Whether your project requires a simple microcontroller for basic tasks or a more capable unit for complex automation, our processors are designed to evolve with you. They all share standard Arduino-compatible pin layouts, allowing for easy upgrades and minimal changes as your project requirements grow. This approach also opens future possibilities for supporting additional processors, such as Raspberry Pi.</p>

<ul>
  <li><strong>Universal Connectors:</strong> Each processor uses standardized pin layouts and connectors, ensuring compatibility with all UltiBlox components. Upgrading the processor is straightforward and requires minimal rewiring.</li>
  <li><strong>Flexible Options:</strong> From basic Arduino-based microcontrollers to more advanced processors, UltiBlox offers choices tailored to different project needs, allowing for growth and adaptation.</li>
</ul>

<h3>Easy Integration</h3>
<p><strong>Modular Upgrades:</strong> Though based on Arduino circuit standards, processors are easy to upgrade. You can start with a basic setup and transition to a more powerful unit as your project develops, keeping wiring changes to a minimum.</p>
<p><strong>Consistent Programming Experience:</strong> All processors support similar programming workflows, making upgrades seamless without the need to learn new tools or methods.</p>

